---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import StripeQuote from '../components/StripeQuote.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Spotsylvania RFC"
  description="Learn about the vision, phased approach, and founding story behind Spotsylvania Rugby Football Club."
  ogTitle="About Spotsylvania RFC"
  ogDescription="The vision, phased approach, and founding story behind Spotsylvania Rugby Football Club — a traditional club in formation."
>
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content">

    <div class="ph-outer">
      <div class="ph-inner">
        <p class="section-label">About the Club</p>
        <h1 class="section-title">A club <em>worth building.</em></h1>
        <p class="section-body">
          Spotsylvania RFC is not a programme, a league, or a seasonal activity. The goal is a
          traditional rugby football club — one that starts small, earns its place, and grows into
          something permanent.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <p class="section-label">The Vision</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">More than a <em>sport.</em></h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        Rugby has a culture unlike anything else — forged through hard training, honest competition,
        respect for opponents, and fellowship after the final whistle. The aim is to bring that
        tradition to Spotsylvania in a way that forms character, welcomes families, and gives local
        players a badge to earn. Unity, courage, and service are not slogans here; they describe
        what rugby at its best actually produces.
      </p>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <h3 class="sub-heading">All levels welcome</h3>
          <p>
            No experience necessary. Rugby rewards courage, effort, and teachability as much as
            raw skill. Complete beginners are the target audience, not the exception.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="sub-heading">A club for life</h3>
          <p>
            From first practice to coaching the next generation, a good rugby club grows with its
            members. The goal is something permanent — not a flash-in-the-pan seasonal programme.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="sub-heading">Real fellowship</h3>
          <p>
            The fellowship after the match is part of the game. What begins on the pitch — trust,
            grit, shared effort — can become friendship that lasts for decades.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="sub-heading">Rooted locally</h3>
          <p>
            This club should belong to this community. We may compete regionally, but our identity
            should be shaped by the people and place we call home.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-alt">
      <p class="section-label">The Approach</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Start with <em>exposure.</em><br />Build toward play.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        A club cannot start at the top. The plan is phased — beginning where the barriers are
        lowest and building from there as interest, volunteers, and resources develop.
      </p>

      <ol class="phase-list">
        <li class="phase-item">
          <div class="phase-num" aria-hidden="true">01</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Exposure &amp; Interest</h3>
            <p>
              Youth tag rugby in local schools and community spaces. Non-contact. Open to beginners.
              The first goal is to put rugby in front of players and families who have never seen it
              played. School demonstrations, after-school sessions, and community days are the tools.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="phase-item">
          <div class="phase-num" aria-hidden="true">02</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Touch &amp; Flag</h3>
            <p>
              Structured touch and flag rugby with regular sessions, basic skill development, and
              small-sided games. Players begin to learn the laws, positions, and culture of the game
              in a safe, progressive format. This is also when adult interest can begin to organise.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="phase-item">
          <div class="phase-num" aria-hidden="true">03</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Registered Club Play</h3>
            <p>
              Full club registration with USA Rugby, competitive fixtures, trained coaches and
              referees, and the infrastructure of a proper rugby football club. Youth and adult
              pathways develop in parallel as numbers allow. This is the destination — not the
              starting point.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <p class="section-label">Coaching &amp; Character</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Teach the game <em>properly.</em></h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        Rugby coaching at the founding level is about building habits — safe technique, honest
        effort, respect for teammates and opponents. Winning matters, but it follows from doing
        things right, not the other way around.
      </p>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <h3 class="sub-heading">Player development first</h3>
          <p>
            Sessions will be structured around progressive skill development. Players who start
            with no experience should leave each session understanding one thing they did not know
            before.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="sub-heading">No experience required — to coach</h3>
          <p>
            Many of the best youth coaches in rugby came from other sports. What matters is
            willingness to learn, patience with beginners, and a genuine interest in players'
            development. Coaching courses and mentorship are available.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <StripeQuote />

    <section class="section">
      <p class="section-label">Founding Story</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Why <em>now.</em> Why here.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        Spotsylvania County is growing. Sports programmes exist, but rugby — with its particular
        combination of physical development, teamwork, discipline, and culture — is not part of the
        local landscape. That gap is the reason Spotsylvania RFC is being built.
      </p>
      <p class="prose">
        This is a founding interest effort. There is no club yet — there is a goal, a plan, and a
        list of people who have said they want to see it happen. The founding list exists to measure
        whether there is enough real interest to move forward. Every name on it represents someone
        who believed a rugby club was worth having here before one existed.
      </p>
      <p class="prose">
        If interest is sufficient, the first step is an interest meeting where players, parents,
        coaches, and supporters can meet, ask questions, and decide together what the first season
        looks like. Nothing before that meeting is a commitment — it is an expression of interest,
        and that is exactly what is needed right now.
      </p>
      <a href="/#interest" class="btn-primary">Join the Founding List</a>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ph-outer {
    background: var(--green);
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .ph-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: calc(var(--section-pad-v) + 52px) 0 var(--section-pad-v);
  }

  .ph-outer .section-label {
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .ph-outer .section-title {
    color: var(--cream);
  }

  .ph-outer .section-title em {
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .ph-outer .section-body {
    color: rgba(246, 242, 230, 0.75);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section-alt {
    background: var(--light);
  }

  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 40px 60px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .sub-heading {
    font-family: 'Oswald', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .two-col p,
  .prose {
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .phase-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 48px 0 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .phase-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 40px;
    padding: 36px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(30, 61, 46, 0.12);
  }

  .phase-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(30, 61, 46, 0.12);
  }

  .phase-item p {
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .phase-num {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--gold);
    opacity: 0.55;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    line-height: 1;
    padding-top: 4px;
    min-width: 52px;
  }
</style>
